WEBVTT

00:06.320 --> 00:08.880
[scrap dealer shouting]

00:08.000 --> 00:18.000
সাইট খুঁজে না পেলে ব্রাউজারে লিখুন:
-=[ MyFlixBD.com ]=-

00:12.320 --> 00:16.400
[shopkeeper] 500 grand.
You get 500 grand for armpit burns.

00:16.480 --> 00:19.000
[Ani] Only if Mr Banaspati wins the case.

00:19.080 --> 00:22.200
But for that,
we're going to need your help, sir.

00:22.280 --> 00:25.480
Uncle, all you have to do is say in court

00:25.560 --> 00:28.240
that I bought all my Fire Clone Dios
from you.

00:28.320 --> 00:29.600
Wrong.

00:31.120 --> 00:34.120
You never bought those deodorants
from him. You just took them.

00:34.200 --> 00:36.440
Therefore, you are not a consumer.

00:36.520 --> 00:39.320
And therefore, you have no case
to take to the consumer court.

00:39.400 --> 00:41.680
[chuckles] That kind of thing
may work abroad,

00:41.760 --> 00:45.200
but I was raised differently.
Why would I pay my own uncle?

00:46.280 --> 00:47.960
[groans] Give me that, you fool.

00:48.040 --> 00:51.320
He's been saying the same thing
and freeloading off me for years.

00:51.400 --> 00:53.480
Madam, he can't even afford face cream

00:53.560 --> 00:55.600
but insists on using moisturiser.

00:55.680 --> 00:58.560
[Banaspati] Uncle, I only do it
because you are family.

00:58.640 --> 01:02.360
Now, what good is a family
if there's no give and take between us?

01:03.240 --> 01:05.000
- [shopkeeper] Hey.
- Toxic.

01:05.560 --> 01:06.720
Thank you.

01:06.800 --> 01:08.240
- But not illegal.
- Mmm.

01:08.320 --> 01:12.840
The Consumer Court will completely
understand this arrangement, sir.

01:12.920 --> 01:16.240
And Mr Banaspati has promised
to settle all his old dues

01:16.320 --> 01:18.760
with the money he receives
as compensation.

01:18.840 --> 01:21.720
All he'll do is clear your past dues
with 500 grand.

01:21.800 --> 01:23.320
If you testify on my client's behalf,

01:23.400 --> 01:25.520
I'll make you a distributor for Firestore.

01:25.600 --> 01:27.960
- No, I'm not interested.
- Ask for whatever you want.

01:28.040 --> 01:29.040
One second.

01:29.120 --> 01:30.520
Sir, ask me for whatever you want.

01:30.600 --> 01:32.080
[Vishwas coughing]

01:32.160 --> 01:35.880
Except financial or personal favours
of any kind.

01:37.320 --> 01:38.320
[sighs]

01:39.040 --> 01:41.920
They are sending my son to jail.

01:42.000 --> 01:44.240
Please save him, madam.

01:45.000 --> 01:48.440
Otherwise, Kumar and Sons
will be reduced to just Kumar.

01:48.520 --> 01:51.280
They're not sending him to jail.
He's already in jail.

01:51.360 --> 01:52.480
Make up your mind for God's sake.

01:53.280 --> 01:56.040
Yes. He is in jail, juvenile jail.

01:56.920 --> 01:58.440
He still has six months to serve.

02:00.200 --> 02:02.200
They are saying he'll go to an adult jail.

02:04.440 --> 02:08.000
Now, whoever manages to save my son,

02:08.080 --> 02:09.960
I'll testify on her behalf.

02:12.560 --> 02:15.680
Sir, a juvenile is being tried
as an adult.

02:15.760 --> 02:17.840
Sorry. What has he done that…

02:17.920 --> 02:19.880
Ani, you will figure it out.
You are from Harvard.

02:19.960 --> 02:21.840
- Come on, come on. Let's go.
- Thank you, sir.

02:22.600 --> 02:24.160
- A crow.
- Where?

02:24.800 --> 02:26.680
- Where is it?
- There.

02:26.760 --> 02:28.160
Where?

02:28.760 --> 02:29.840
[laughs]

02:29.920 --> 02:31.680
What the hell, Banaspati?

02:31.760 --> 02:33.480
Where you off to, you idiot?

02:33.560 --> 02:35.080
[theme song playing]

02:47.560 --> 02:49.720
[Shubhkela] I'm a judge, I can't
be expected to do nonsense like this.

02:49.800 --> 02:51.200
- [knocks on door]
- Mr Tyagi,

02:51.280 --> 02:54.360
when I asked you to let me know if
there was anything I could help you with,

02:54.440 --> 02:56.360
- this is certainly not what I meant.
- [Tyagi] Huh?

02:56.440 --> 02:58.560
What is this? This is ridiculous.

02:59.640 --> 03:01.280
You want me to judge short films?

03:01.360 --> 03:03.800
- Mr Kela, this is Mr Dua…
- [gasps]

03:03.880 --> 03:05.760
…the Patparganj Legal Services Secretary.

03:05.840 --> 03:08.360
- Namaste.
- Namaste.

03:08.440 --> 03:13.360
The one in charge of organising
the short film competition is him.

03:15.640 --> 03:17.280
I see. [chuckles]

03:17.360 --> 03:19.800
I've been very keen to meet you.
[chuckles]

03:19.880 --> 03:21.480
You're doing a very noble thing, sir.

03:21.560 --> 03:23.040
- For the High Court, sir.
- [chuckles] I see.

03:23.120 --> 03:26.000
What they feel is
that only through the medium of film

03:26.080 --> 03:28.000
can legal awareness be created.

03:28.080 --> 03:29.400
So, Mr. Kela, you will judge, right?

03:29.480 --> 03:31.000
Please, Your Honour.

03:31.080 --> 03:33.840
It's not good to delay when it comes
to matters of the High Court.

03:33.920 --> 03:35.120
Of course.

03:35.200 --> 03:39.080
Uh… But, uh… Since we're talking
about society's progress,

03:39.160 --> 03:41.320
shouldn't there be more than one judge?

03:41.400 --> 03:42.600
So join us, Mr Tyagi?

03:43.720 --> 03:45.840
We can't do this without the PDJ, right?

03:45.920 --> 03:47.000
Of course.

03:48.040 --> 03:49.080
Of course.

03:49.160 --> 03:50.640
But I'm sure you know that

03:50.720 --> 03:52.640
as admin, I have so many responsibilities.

03:52.720 --> 03:55.680
Look at the pile of files here
and the ones Topo's carrying.

03:55.760 --> 03:57.080
I have to sign them all.

03:57.160 --> 03:59.120
Otherwise, I would have watched the films.

03:59.200 --> 04:00.200
Your Honour.

04:00.720 --> 04:02.640
Yeah, tell me.

04:02.720 --> 04:06.000
You had said there is no way that
you would do this kind of ridiculous work.

04:08.400 --> 04:11.000
But if you're keen on
watching the films, then…

04:12.120 --> 04:14.240
- go ahead.
- No, no, no. Uh, Topo…

04:15.840 --> 04:18.920
I was just joking.
You know how I'm always cracking jokes.

04:20.560 --> 04:21.760
Oh, that was a joke.

04:24.040 --> 04:25.480
I get it, Your Honour.

04:25.560 --> 04:26.800
- What?
- I get it.

04:26.880 --> 04:30.200
I'll go make preparations for
the screening. We'll watch films today.

04:30.280 --> 04:31.520
Listen! You…

04:31.600 --> 04:33.840
You mean you'll watch the films with us?

04:33.920 --> 04:35.560
Yes, of course he will.

04:36.200 --> 04:38.160
- Yes. Why not?
- Won't he?

04:38.240 --> 04:42.320
Sir, if you don't mind,
which was the last film you watched?

04:43.120 --> 04:44.320
[Shubhkela] Which one, Tyagi?

04:45.720 --> 04:47.440
The Cutting Edge of Revenge Part 2.

04:54.200 --> 04:55.440
[phone buzzes, beeps]

04:55.520 --> 04:56.360
BEENU

04:57.120 --> 04:58.120
[Ghosh] Defence.

05:00.040 --> 05:01.080
Defence!

05:02.000 --> 05:03.000
Why isn't he listening?

05:03.080 --> 05:05.520
Mr Lakhmir Singh Balli!

05:05.600 --> 05:06.600
Yes!

05:07.560 --> 05:10.320
[stammers] What I meant, Your Honour,
is objection.

05:11.680 --> 05:13.400
Your opening statement is what I need.

05:13.480 --> 05:15.480
[laughing]

05:16.760 --> 05:17.800
- What is this?
- [gavel bangs]

05:17.880 --> 05:20.720
Your eyes were glued to your phone
the whole time. I made a mistake.

05:20.800 --> 05:22.280
I should have gone to Miss Sujata first.

05:22.360 --> 05:23.880
And you,
don't you dare try calling me again, sir.

05:23.960 --> 05:25.720
- Sir! Sorry.
- Sorry, it won't happen again, sir!

05:25.800 --> 05:27.760
- Sorry, sir. Sorry.
- [chuckles]

05:27.840 --> 05:29.120
Now what do you think?

05:29.200 --> 05:31.160
Was the fake idea a childish idea?

05:31.240 --> 05:32.840
This is fun, Law. [chuckles]

05:32.920 --> 05:35.560
Beenu Bindra isn't going
to allow Mintu to work.

05:35.640 --> 05:36.640
Wanna see some magic?

05:36.720 --> 05:38.320
- BEENU, I MISS YOU.
- MISS YOU TOO, DARLING.

05:38.400 --> 05:40.280
\[phone chiming]

05:41.400 --> 05:42.680
[chuckles]

05:49.840 --> 05:51.240
[laughing]

05:56.680 --> 05:57.800
Pawan…

06:05.720 --> 06:06.840
Listen to me.

06:06.920 --> 06:08.360
There are serious charges against you.

06:08.440 --> 06:11.480
They're saying you tried
to grievously injure a probation officer.

06:11.560 --> 06:13.720
I gave him such a hard shove

06:13.800 --> 06:15.640
that he bounced down the stairs
like a football.

06:16.600 --> 06:18.880
I took responsibility for it
on social media.

06:19.960 --> 06:20.960
He's shameless.

06:21.600 --> 06:23.640
[Ani] I can understand, Pawan.

06:23.720 --> 06:26.480
But why shove him like that?

06:27.080 --> 06:28.120
Was he abusive?

06:28.960 --> 06:30.720
Look, there's no scope in a juvenile jail.

06:31.560 --> 06:33.840
About a year ago,
I was caught for stealing.

06:41.840 --> 06:43.120
I wasn't very good at it,

06:44.480 --> 06:46.000
but I learnt after I came here.

06:46.080 --> 06:47.520
- [gasps]
- [stammers]

06:48.080 --> 06:49.560
Pawan, give it to me!

06:49.640 --> 06:50.600
- Pa--
- [gasps]

06:50.680 --> 06:53.160
[Pawan] But do you know what?
I'm done with petty crime.

06:53.240 --> 06:55.800
I want to commit big crimes.

06:55.880 --> 06:56.880
[Vishwas] Move.

06:59.400 --> 07:02.400
So you're not being sent to Tihar jail.

07:02.480 --> 07:03.920
You actually want to go there.

07:04.000 --> 07:06.080
- 'Cause that's my school.
- Ridiculous.

07:06.160 --> 07:10.640
[Pawan] Rinku Moghiya,
Lucky Shamshera, Montu Billa…

07:10.720 --> 07:11.920
Montu Billa, yeah.

07:12.000 --> 07:13.360
- That's where all my teachers are…
- Really?

07:13.440 --> 07:15.720
…where my dreams will come true.

07:15.800 --> 07:17.200
[Ani] What's wrong with you, Pawan?

07:17.280 --> 07:19.240
In the land of Mahatma Gandhi,

07:19.320 --> 07:21.120
how can you idolise gangsters?

07:22.040 --> 07:23.800
Crime never pays.

07:23.880 --> 07:25.880
What was Gandhi's net worth?

07:26.840 --> 07:28.680
- Mahatma Gandhi's net worth.
- [phone beeps]

07:29.400 --> 07:30.720
Escobar

07:31.840 --> 07:35.000
was the seventh richest man in the world.

07:35.080 --> 07:37.120
[Ani] Look, Pawan, you are just 16.

07:37.200 --> 07:39.400
You can still change your mind.

07:40.000 --> 07:42.120
You should make something of yourself.

07:42.200 --> 07:43.800
[Nayana] Contribute to society.

07:43.880 --> 07:45.160
You're still a child, you know.

07:45.240 --> 07:46.680
Hey!

07:46.760 --> 07:48.640
Don't ever abuse me like that again.

07:54.040 --> 07:55.400
I'm a man, okay?

07:57.360 --> 07:59.280
And I don't want a lawyer. Get out!

07:59.360 --> 08:00.360
- Listen--
- [Pawan] Out!

08:00.440 --> 08:01.440
One minute.

08:04.400 --> 08:06.120
I had a brat of a nephew just like him.

08:08.640 --> 08:10.680
- Sorted him out.
- [toy gun beeps]

08:11.560 --> 08:13.320
[Vishwas] Ladies, wait outside.

08:16.680 --> 08:17.680
So, bro,

08:18.760 --> 08:19.920
what's your problem?

08:20.840 --> 08:22.840
- [door opens]
- [items clattering]

08:23.400 --> 08:25.680
What the hell, man?
What kind of behaviour is this?

08:25.760 --> 08:27.640
- [Pawan] Get lost, you wimp.
- [whimpering]

08:35.000 --> 08:36.960
Do I look like a wimp to you?

08:37.040 --> 08:39.680
Vishwas, that's politically incorrect.

08:39.760 --> 08:42.040
Will you stop lecturing for once, Ani?

08:42.120 --> 08:43.160
Thank you.

08:43.240 --> 08:44.880
If Pawan keeps behaving like this,

08:44.960 --> 08:47.480
then no judge is going to treat him
like a minor.

08:47.560 --> 08:49.720
- And I will not get my testimony.
- [Vishwas sighs]

08:49.800 --> 08:52.400
We're talking about
a child's future here, guys.

08:52.920 --> 08:54.680
His entire life could be ruined.

08:56.000 --> 08:57.480
And my entire day.

08:58.960 --> 09:00.200
[scoffs]

09:00.680 --> 09:01.680
Unless…

09:04.840 --> 09:07.440
Oh, yes, sir. The film just started.

09:07.960 --> 09:11.480
And guess what?
The PDJ himself is sitting and judging it.

09:12.200 --> 09:14.280
Thanks. Okay, I'll talk to you later.

09:14.360 --> 09:15.840
I am getting a bit nervous.

09:16.520 --> 09:19.840
[yawns]

09:21.480 --> 09:22.960
Topo, I am done with these.

09:24.040 --> 09:25.040
- Topo.
- Hmm?

09:25.840 --> 09:27.440
The first lot is done, Your Honour.

09:29.240 --> 09:33.440
[actor] Not bad, Ravi! You're not just
a thief, but a script writer too.

09:33.520 --> 09:34.720
[actor 2] How can you say that, sir?

09:34.800 --> 09:38.800
The judge's pen is so powerful that
whenever he uses it, he rewrites destiny.

09:38.880 --> 09:41.560
Listen, this film should
definitely be disqualified.

09:41.640 --> 09:43.760
This judge's pen is exhausted.

09:43.840 --> 09:46.440
It's run out of ink signing all day
and now this?

09:46.960 --> 09:49.160
Now take a look at the power of my pen.

09:49.800 --> 09:52.920
It's deciding the best fresh face… [yawns]

09:53.000 --> 09:55.160
…handling 100 cases a day,

09:55.240 --> 09:56.840
issuing 50 orders,

09:56.920 --> 10:00.240
then translating old judgment
from English to Hindi.

10:00.320 --> 10:02.320
There's so much stress

10:02.400 --> 10:05.960
that I have to attend a mandatory stress
relief workshop that too on a Sunday.

10:06.040 --> 10:08.800
Do you know what kind of decisions
I am making?

10:08.880 --> 10:09.920
Huh?

10:12.360 --> 10:17.360
Which gate at Patparganj
will require 32 mm lock on it,

10:17.440 --> 10:20.920
and which gate will require
60 mm lock on it?

10:21.000 --> 10:23.360
- [chuckles]
- That's what I'm deciding here. Huh?

10:23.440 --> 10:25.320
[yawns]

10:25.400 --> 10:29.280
I heard that after becoming a judge,
that's when you get a real kick.

10:29.360 --> 10:30.480
What?

10:31.160 --> 10:33.720
That it's a real kick when you're a judge.

10:34.440 --> 10:36.680
I don't know when
that kick will come to me.

10:37.480 --> 10:38.840
Oh, sorry.

10:40.000 --> 10:41.000
One,

10:42.000 --> 10:43.040
zero.

10:43.760 --> 10:46.080
You mean pen fight? Huh?

10:46.160 --> 10:47.360
Pen fight?

10:48.360 --> 10:50.120
And then they should…

10:51.720 --> 10:53.520
\- [phone chimes]
- [Mintu] Division bench decided.

10:53.600 --> 10:54.520
\SUJATA NEGI

11:00.960 --> 11:02.200
[shutter clicks]

11:02.280 --> 11:03.280
[phone buzzes]

11:07.320 --> 11:08.760
[Law] Ew.

11:08.840 --> 11:11.560
Look, he's showing you his nose hair.

11:12.200 --> 11:14.800
He's such a despo. He'll definitely agree.

11:14.880 --> 11:17.360
Look, I agree that
Mintu is still very single,

11:17.440 --> 11:19.840
but not enough to blow all his money
on an unknown girl.

11:21.600 --> 11:22.920
It's my mom's birthday.

11:24.080 --> 11:25.680
A toaster's 850.

11:25.760 --> 11:27.160
What a cheapskate you are.

11:27.240 --> 11:28.240
[Law clicks tongue]

11:29.800 --> 11:32.520
- Hey. Client.
- He looks loaded.

11:33.120 --> 11:35.320
Listen. We are in this for the long run,
so don't act cheap now.

11:35.400 --> 11:36.880
- Okay.
- Hello, sir.

11:36.960 --> 11:38.880
- Your chamber?
- Uh, yes, sir.

11:38.960 --> 11:41.320
It is very busy here.
Let's have coffee outside, sir.

11:41.400 --> 11:43.280
- Let's go.
- [phone chiming]

11:55.000 --> 11:56.520
\BEENU: LISTEN.
I NEED 850 RUPEES

11:56.600 --> 11:57.880
\CAN YOU SEND ME THE MONEY?

12:02.520 --> 12:03.520
Law, my boy.

12:04.720 --> 12:05.760
Yes, sir?

12:06.640 --> 12:08.120
There is this client of mine.

12:09.200 --> 12:10.280
Who?

12:12.320 --> 12:13.320
Nintu.

12:14.720 --> 12:15.960
- Nintu.
- The thing is

12:16.040 --> 12:18.360
he's been getting very friendly
with some girl online.

12:18.440 --> 12:19.360
[Law] Mmm.

12:19.440 --> 12:21.920
But now the problem is
she's asking for money.

12:22.440 --> 12:26.360
And as much as 850 rupees. You think
she could be a fake or a scamster?

12:26.440 --> 12:27.840
850?

12:28.960 --> 12:30.000
Yeah.

12:30.760 --> 12:32.760
If she was fake,
she would have asked for thousands.

12:35.440 --> 12:37.440
But what if she's genuine? Hmm?

12:39.040 --> 12:42.240
What a huge loss it would be for Nintu.

12:42.320 --> 12:43.320
Just think.

12:45.280 --> 12:47.280
And maybe she needs it very badly.

12:48.400 --> 12:50.520
A birthday gift for her mom.

12:51.400 --> 12:53.920
I'm sure you know
how expensive toasters are these days.

12:56.840 --> 12:58.640
You're so right, Law.

12:58.720 --> 13:00.160
One shouldn't take a risk.

13:00.840 --> 13:03.480
What I'll do is I'll send her another 200…

13:05.480 --> 13:06.440
Meaning he'll send.

13:10.200 --> 13:11.920
- [phone chimes]
- [phone buzzes]

13:20.040 --> 13:21.680
[chuckling]

13:21.760 --> 13:23.280
[Shambhu] The match has reached
a critical stage.

13:23.360 --> 13:25.680
Mr Tyagi's pen is
at the edge of the table.

13:25.760 --> 13:27.760
And at the other end,
Topo's ready to play.

13:31.040 --> 13:33.800
Oh shit, man. Just missed it.

13:33.880 --> 13:35.440
- Just missed it.
- Damn.

13:35.520 --> 13:37.800
Topo, you're pushing too far
with the arse-licking.

13:38.520 --> 13:41.920
Guys, in the pen fight,
there are no judges, stenos or readers.

13:42.000 --> 13:43.480
We are all equal. Okay?

13:43.560 --> 13:45.840
No way that's possible.
You are Your Honour.

13:45.920 --> 13:47.040
Yeah, that's okay.

13:47.120 --> 13:50.000
Your Honour is issuing an order that
we are all equal here.

13:50.080 --> 13:52.240
We are players, okay? Let's play now.

13:52.320 --> 13:54.160
- Okay, Tyagi. Let's play.
- Hmm?

13:54.240 --> 13:55.680
- What?
- What?

13:56.600 --> 14:00.240
Mr Tyagi, you just said that
we are equal players here.

14:02.000 --> 14:03.040
But I have one condition.

14:04.080 --> 14:08.800
The team that loses treats everyone
to Jaggi's famous lentil curry.

14:09.880 --> 14:11.480
With some crispy flatbread.

14:11.560 --> 14:12.560
Okay, now…

14:14.200 --> 14:15.240
[Shubhkela] What?

14:16.160 --> 14:17.720
Let's just play, man.

14:29.440 --> 14:31.520
[cheering]

14:32.960 --> 14:34.720
Amazing.

14:34.800 --> 14:36.640
Looks like they found a winning film.

14:37.760 --> 14:39.200
[slurping]

14:39.280 --> 14:41.960
Sir, you are the probation officer.

14:42.560 --> 14:44.920
It's your testimony
that holds the most weight.

14:45.000 --> 14:47.360
Why are you pushing for Pawan
to go to jail?

14:48.040 --> 14:52.000
What do you think? Hmm? You think
I enjoy sitting with a crooked neck?

14:52.720 --> 14:55.160
This neck brace is
some kind of fashion statement?

14:55.240 --> 14:57.280
Sir, please excuse her. She's dumb.

14:58.320 --> 15:01.000
In certain special cases,
the law makes an exception

15:01.080 --> 15:03.000
where they treat a 16-year-old
as an adult.

15:03.080 --> 15:05.600
Listen, listen. The ways of the law
are beyond my understanding.

15:06.240 --> 15:08.520
A 16-year-old kid is allowed to work

15:08.000 --> 15:18.000
Downloaded from -=[ MyFlixBD.com ]=-

15:08.600 --> 15:10.600
but cannot commit a crime till he's 18.

15:11.400 --> 15:14.040
An 18-year-old can vote
and form a government,

15:14.120 --> 15:16.840
but he can't pour himself a drink
till he's 25.

15:16.920 --> 15:18.240
- Now you tell me. Please.
- Sure. Me?

15:18.320 --> 15:21.400
Does drinking require
more intelligence than voting?

15:22.960 --> 15:24.200
- Yes, sir.
- Huh?

15:24.280 --> 15:28.240
Because when you drink, the slightest
change in proportion changes everything.

15:28.320 --> 15:31.120
But you can vote for anyone you want.
It changes nothing.

15:31.200 --> 15:32.120
[chuckles]

15:32.200 --> 15:33.560
[groans]

15:34.280 --> 15:36.120
- It's a fact.
- Look, madam.

15:36.200 --> 15:39.520
Those who don't understand
the consequences of their actions

15:39.600 --> 15:40.800
are considered children?

15:41.840 --> 15:45.840
Do you know what Pawan began shouting
after he pushed me down the stairs?

15:46.360 --> 15:48.720
"Tihar, here I come!"

15:50.040 --> 15:51.240
Sir,

15:51.320 --> 15:55.440
Pawan wants to go to Tihar jail, because
gangsters gets more likes on social media.

15:56.200 --> 15:58.440
He doesn't really know
what actually happens there.

15:58.520 --> 16:00.240
- And do you know what's happening here?
- [hip-hop music playing]

16:00.320 --> 16:02.720
These kids are acting like gangsters.

16:03.240 --> 16:07.440
They go "what a wow wow wow,
what a wow wow" like hip-hop stars.

16:07.520 --> 16:09.400
[children whooping]

16:09.480 --> 16:11.960
Hey, hey, hey. What are you doing?
Put that down!

16:12.040 --> 16:13.680
Get out! Go on! Get lost!

16:18.160 --> 16:19.360
Hey, fatso! Move up.

16:20.040 --> 16:21.480
That's Miss Nishigandha.

16:22.240 --> 16:23.560
She comes everyday to teach.

16:23.640 --> 16:25.880
Earlier the kids enjoyed studying.

16:25.960 --> 16:30.000
But now under Pawan's influence,
not a single kid comes to class.

16:30.800 --> 16:32.080
Look, madam,

16:32.160 --> 16:34.720
I agree with you that
every child is special,

16:35.360 --> 16:37.320
but not every child is a child.

16:38.080 --> 16:39.920
According to the JJ Act,

16:40.000 --> 16:44.000
a probation officer's job is to mentor
and guide young delinquents.

16:44.080 --> 16:45.440
And you're judging them.

16:46.280 --> 16:48.400
Sir, if you don't give Pawan a chance,

16:48.480 --> 16:50.080
then how will he reform?

16:50.680 --> 16:51.840
All right.

16:51.920 --> 16:52.920
Huh?

16:53.000 --> 16:54.160
I'm giving him a chance.

16:55.520 --> 16:57.160
According to you, Pawan is a child.

16:57.240 --> 16:58.560
- Yeah.
- Right?

16:58.640 --> 17:01.240
So, what do children say
when they make a mistake?

17:03.280 --> 17:04.280
Sorry.

17:06.840 --> 17:07.840
Sorry.

17:08.560 --> 17:09.520
Now call Pawan.

17:10.360 --> 17:11.680
If he says sorry to me,

17:12.320 --> 17:15.120
I'll happily come to court
and testify in his favour.

17:16.200 --> 17:19.440
I'll tell the court that
he shouldn't be tried as an adult.

17:19.520 --> 17:20.800
But will he say sorry?

17:22.480 --> 17:23.560
Hmm?

17:24.200 --> 17:26.680
How do you get a bully to say he's sorry?

17:26.760 --> 17:28.280
- [phone beeps]
- Hey, wimp!

17:29.240 --> 17:31.080
You… I'm going to…

17:31.160 --> 17:32.280
- I swear.
- Vishwas…

17:32.360 --> 17:34.800
- Ani, stop me before I--
- [Pawan] Sir, embarrass yourself enough?

17:34.880 --> 17:36.760
Are you going to leave
or should I kick you out?

17:36.840 --> 17:38.040
Pawan.

17:38.880 --> 17:41.600
You're just dying to go to Tihar Jail,
aren't you?

17:43.920 --> 17:45.040
Let's go.

17:47.000 --> 17:48.440
[Vishwas] Come on, idiot.

17:48.520 --> 17:51.320
Yay! Tihar, here I come.

17:51.400 --> 17:52.400
Yay!

17:52.920 --> 17:53.920
[phone chimes, buzzes]

17:54.640 --> 17:56.400
BEENU: I THINK YOU'VE EXHAUSTED
YOUR COMPLIMENT QUOTA

17:56.480 --> 17:57.480
[Sujata] Law!

17:58.040 --> 18:00.040
I sealed the deal with that client.

18:01.000 --> 18:03.480
- I just billed him 150 grand.
- Not bad.

18:03.560 --> 18:05.640
[sighs] Bless you, Mintu.

18:06.920 --> 18:08.240
But ma'am,

18:08.320 --> 18:11.240
it's Mintu Sir who will be sponsoring
our celebration.

18:11.320 --> 18:12.760
Check this out.

18:14.360 --> 18:18.240
You know, uh, I really thought
Mintu would turn out to be a creep,

18:18.840 --> 18:20.120
but he's so sentimental.

18:20.200 --> 18:23.160
And all these heart emojis
on his messages.

18:23.240 --> 18:25.120
- He sent me a poem.
- [phone buzzes]

18:25.200 --> 18:28.120
And now he wants
to talk about something personal.

18:28.200 --> 18:29.440
Hold on, he's typing.

18:30.080 --> 18:31.120
- [phone chimes, buzzes]
- Here it is.

18:31.200 --> 18:35.720
"I don't want to start off
our relationship with a lie."

18:35.800 --> 18:37.200
[chortles]

18:37.280 --> 18:38.880
- [phone chimes, buzzes]
- "I am divorcee."

18:39.920 --> 18:41.040
[phone chimes, buzzes]

18:41.120 --> 18:44.760
"If you have a problem with that,
let me know."

18:45.920 --> 18:46.960
[phone chimes, buzzes]

18:47.040 --> 18:49.160
"But I feel very lonely."

18:51.480 --> 18:53.000
[laughs]

18:54.120 --> 18:55.880
What a sad little loner.

18:56.640 --> 18:57.800
What's so funny?

18:58.920 --> 19:01.360
Why is this client's file lying here
on the table?

19:02.520 --> 19:03.520
Go make some copies.

19:18.200 --> 19:20.600
[door opens]

19:20.680 --> 19:22.920
This is the second time this year
I'm coming here.

19:23.000 --> 19:24.800
Come on, come on. Yeah, enough.

19:27.760 --> 19:28.880
Well done, Ani.

19:29.440 --> 19:32.680
I'm going to tell his father that
coming to Tihar was your idea.

19:32.760 --> 19:34.000
If it works,

19:35.000 --> 19:36.160
which it won't.

19:36.240 --> 19:37.400
What's with her?

19:37.480 --> 19:38.480
It will.

19:39.320 --> 19:40.600
[officer] You have only five minutes.

19:40.680 --> 19:42.360
[Vishwas] Sir, we will be done
in two minutes.

19:43.200 --> 19:44.920
Hey, you Skeletor.

19:45.000 --> 19:46.240
- Watch where you're going.
- Sorry, sorry.

19:46.320 --> 19:48.240
- Sorry about that.
- Vishwas. Go talk to her.

19:49.160 --> 19:50.560
Yeah, well, listen.

19:51.080 --> 19:53.720
You won't be able to sleep a wink here
like you do over there.

19:54.440 --> 19:57.200
Instead of 100, 300 men sleep together
stuck to each other.

19:58.600 --> 20:00.400
And bathrooms. Just one.

20:00.920 --> 20:02.400
What will you do in an emergency?

20:02.480 --> 20:04.240
Dude, you'll be shitting your pants.

20:04.760 --> 20:06.560
- Shitting your pants?
- [Vishwas] Hmm.

20:08.760 --> 20:09.960
Come on.

20:10.040 --> 20:11.040
[Ani clears throat]

20:13.160 --> 20:17.200
A king is only as big
as the kingdom he rules.

20:17.280 --> 20:18.600
[Vishwas, Nayana] Right.

20:18.680 --> 20:19.920
No, no… Wrong.

20:21.520 --> 20:23.800
Does he think
this is some kind of promotion?

20:25.360 --> 20:28.600
You won't meet your parents
like you used to in the juvenile home.

20:28.680 --> 20:30.600
At least think about
your mother and father.

20:32.480 --> 20:33.640
I did that.

20:34.840 --> 20:37.160
I have watched my mother crying every day.

20:38.840 --> 20:40.560
Watching her made me want to cry too.

20:40.640 --> 20:41.640
Aw…

20:41.720 --> 20:43.840
- [Vishwas] It's okay, man.
- Now tell me something.

20:43.920 --> 20:46.120
Who will pay ransom to a weeping gangster?

20:47.080 --> 20:49.000
Thank God she can't visit me here.

20:49.080 --> 20:50.120
[scoffs]

20:50.200 --> 20:51.800
[buzzer sounds]

20:51.880 --> 20:53.080
[door creaks open]

20:54.720 --> 20:55.920
Confinement area.

20:56.680 --> 20:59.160
- Come.
- [Vishwas] Oh, my God.

20:59.240 --> 21:01.080
The warden here is very strict.

21:01.160 --> 21:02.200
It's my first time here.

21:02.840 --> 21:04.080
If you break the rules,

21:04.160 --> 21:06.080
they send you
straight to solitary confinement.

21:06.160 --> 21:09.920
You're not allowed to have any kind
of human contact for 15 days, Pawan.

21:10.000 --> 21:11.000
Really?

21:11.640 --> 21:13.520
- You have to stay alone?
- [Vishwas] Mmm.

21:13.600 --> 21:14.800
In the dark?

21:17.920 --> 21:19.440
[prisoner groaning]

21:19.520 --> 21:20.600
[Vishwas] He's shitting.

21:22.240 --> 21:24.800
He's scared. Look, he's shivering.

21:25.520 --> 21:28.360
So, what have you decided, Pawan?

21:30.120 --> 21:31.240
[door opens]

21:33.320 --> 21:34.920
[door closes]

21:36.720 --> 21:37.760
Montu Billa!

21:39.240 --> 21:40.440
Sir, a selfie!

21:40.520 --> 21:41.680
- Please, sir.
- Hey! Catch him.

21:41.760 --> 21:42.880
- Hey!
- Just one selfie. Please, sir.

21:42.960 --> 21:44.520
- How did he get a phone?
- Big fan, sir.

21:44.600 --> 21:46.320
Sir, will you let me join the Billa gang?

21:46.400 --> 21:48.880
I've even thought of some Bollywood actors
I can threaten.

21:48.960 --> 21:51.680
- That's my phone!
- Montu Billa. Sir!

21:51.760 --> 21:52.720
Let me go.

21:52.800 --> 21:53.880
- Sir!
- Come here.

21:53.960 --> 21:56.280
- [door closes]
- Final point.

21:56.360 --> 21:59.600
Topo versus His Honour Kela Sir.

22:01.280 --> 22:02.560
[Maya] Easy. Easy.

22:02.640 --> 22:03.840
- Won't happen.
- Hmm?

22:03.920 --> 22:04.760
Won't happen.

22:10.280 --> 22:11.600
Point! Point! Point!

22:11.680 --> 22:13.640
- [Maya] But who kept the phone there?
- Hey, what point?

22:13.720 --> 22:15.120
- How could it be?
- The pen didn't fall.

22:15.200 --> 22:16.840
- Because the phone stopped it.
- So what?

22:16.920 --> 22:18.880
- Exactly.
- Referee, ask them whose phone that is.

22:19.440 --> 22:20.480
It's Mr Kela's phone.

22:20.560 --> 22:22.480
- Then Mr Kela is a cheater, Your Honour.
- Cheater?

22:22.560 --> 22:24.680
Your Honour, I never cheat when I play.
Why are you cheating so much?

22:24.760 --> 22:26.280
Objection.

22:26.800 --> 22:28.280
Mr Referee.

22:29.000 --> 22:33.520
Did you see Mr. Shubhkela put his phone
on the table in the middle of the game?

22:36.920 --> 22:38.440
The phone was already here.

22:38.520 --> 22:40.600
If you consider this round as cheating,

22:40.680 --> 22:43.080
you will have to consider every round
as cheating

22:43.160 --> 22:45.120
and that includes the particular round

22:46.680 --> 22:48.640
that you yourself just won.

22:48.720 --> 22:52.200
Your Honour,
you are arguing like a lawyer now.

22:53.480 --> 22:55.600
That was pure luck. Concede the point.

22:56.360 --> 23:00.840
Mr Referee, we considered this phone
as part of the game from the very start,

23:00.920 --> 23:04.240
and you could say that
it was always our strategy.

23:04.320 --> 23:07.240
But our opponent claims that it was a

23:07.920 --> 23:09.200
matter of luck,

23:09.880 --> 23:11.680
that is a game of chance.

23:12.360 --> 23:13.360
In other words,

23:14.360 --> 23:15.400
gambling.

23:16.760 --> 23:17.960
Gambling,

23:18.680 --> 23:20.280
that too inside the court.

23:20.360 --> 23:21.360
Oh.

23:21.880 --> 23:24.480
So Mr Topo, what you are trying to say is

23:24.560 --> 23:26.600
that we are gambling inside this court?

23:28.440 --> 23:29.400
No.

23:29.480 --> 23:30.560
So,

23:31.120 --> 23:33.200
it's Mr Shubhkela's turn, right?

23:33.280 --> 23:34.960
Yeah, yeah, yeah. Mr Kela.

23:35.040 --> 23:37.120
- [Tyagi] Hmm.
- [Shubhkela] Let's play.

23:37.200 --> 23:38.200
Topo.

23:40.880 --> 23:43.560
- Okay?
- Yes. Go for it.

23:48.320 --> 23:49.960
[cheering]

23:54.440 --> 23:55.840
Thank you for bringing me here.

23:55.920 --> 23:58.800
Any doubts I had are all clear now.

24:00.120 --> 24:02.080
This is where my future lies.

24:02.160 --> 24:03.320
Tihar.

24:03.400 --> 24:05.120
I told you,

24:05.200 --> 24:06.640
"If it works".

24:07.440 --> 24:08.960
[bell tolling]

24:09.040 --> 24:10.440
ENTRY IS PROHIBITED
WITH RESTRICTED ITEMS

24:11.800 --> 24:14.200
[officer] Come on, come on.
Break's over. Get back to work.

24:14.280 --> 24:15.880
- Move it.
- What nonsense is this?

24:15.960 --> 24:17.240
Mandatory labour.

24:17.760 --> 24:19.120
One has to work here?

24:23.640 --> 24:25.360
[Vishwas] Yes. One has to work here.

24:26.720 --> 24:28.560
But not in a juvenile home

24:28.640 --> 24:30.160
because child labour is illegal.

24:30.800 --> 24:32.320
But they make adults work hard.

24:33.400 --> 24:36.040
Washing vessels, sweeping,
mopping, cleaning the windows,

24:36.120 --> 24:37.920
clearing all the cobwebs, mowing the lawn.

24:38.000 --> 24:39.000
- Weeding--
- Enough.

24:40.680 --> 24:41.920
[chuckles]

24:42.000 --> 24:42.960
Bullshit.

24:54.400 --> 24:55.360
Montu Billa.

24:58.120 --> 25:00.440
Montu Sir is a gangster
and he's doing the dishes?

25:05.320 --> 25:07.080
And why is that Skeletor sitting idle?

25:07.160 --> 25:09.680
Why isn't Montu Sir telling him
to wash the dishes?

25:09.760 --> 25:11.800
That's his plate being washed by Montu.

25:11.880 --> 25:12.880
[Vishwas] Mmm.

25:12.960 --> 25:15.360
- Kiddo, that's Tinu Bansal there.
- [Vishwas] Tinu Bansal!

25:15.440 --> 25:17.000
No wonder he looks so familiar.

25:18.040 --> 25:19.040
- He's a big shot.
- You mean

25:19.120 --> 25:20.720
he's a bigger gangster than Montu Billa?

25:20.800 --> 25:21.800
Yeah, much bigger.

25:22.440 --> 25:25.000
Hey, he's the one who pulled off
the 2021 scam.

25:25.080 --> 25:26.080
- Ah…
- Yes.

25:26.160 --> 25:28.120
The scam was worth 35 billion.

25:28.200 --> 25:32.120
So far only 6 billion has been recovered.
The rest is sitting in a Swiss account.

25:32.640 --> 25:34.760
That's where Montu gets his salary from
every month.

25:34.840 --> 25:35.680
Yeah.

25:35.760 --> 25:37.600
[officer] He's hired Montu for protection.

25:37.680 --> 25:39.720
What do I have to do to become like him?

25:40.520 --> 25:42.160
[clicks tongue, sighs]

25:43.960 --> 25:45.080
A scam.

25:46.120 --> 25:47.960
Nayana, seriously?

25:50.760 --> 25:54.520
And do you know what you have to do
to pull off such a huge financial scam?

25:56.760 --> 25:57.760
Study.

26:01.640 --> 26:04.480
Today was fun. I really had a good time.

26:04.560 --> 26:05.720
Oh…

26:05.800 --> 26:08.920
It wasn't
the pen fight you enjoyed, Tyagi.

26:09.000 --> 26:10.840
- Hmm.
- It was something else.

26:10.920 --> 26:12.120
Really? What?

26:13.080 --> 26:13.960
The arguing.

26:15.720 --> 26:17.200
And we are enjoying the winnings.

26:17.920 --> 26:21.400
That's why I put the phone there
on purpose. [laughs]

26:22.120 --> 26:25.960
Today I realised why your chamber was
the most famous in Patparganj court.

26:27.000 --> 26:30.440
It must have been difficult
leaving your practice to be a judge.

26:34.920 --> 26:37.200
- [Shubhkela] Tyagi?
- Hmm?

26:37.280 --> 26:39.120
You miss practising law, don't you?

26:49.240 --> 26:52.000
Where does he have the time to think
about things like this?

26:52.080 --> 26:53.280
He has so much work.

26:56.760 --> 26:58.080
Uh… Tyagi?

26:58.160 --> 27:01.240
- Try some of that curry. It's really good.
- You're so right, Topo.

27:06.880 --> 27:08.520
- [Pawan sobbing] Please forgive me, sir.
- Hey.

27:08.600 --> 27:09.840
Please. Please forgive me, sir.

27:09.920 --> 27:12.480
I don't want to go there anymore, sir.

27:12.560 --> 27:14.520
Please forgive me, sir. Sir, please.

27:14.600 --> 27:16.080
Okay, I forgive you. Come on, get up.

27:16.160 --> 27:17.760
- I am sorry.
- Get up. Get up.

27:22.720 --> 27:25.520
- You promise to be a good boy?
- Yes, sir.

27:25.600 --> 27:27.120
You promise to study hard.

27:28.760 --> 27:31.240
Of course, sir.
That's the most important thing.

27:31.320 --> 27:32.320
Huh?

27:33.120 --> 27:35.960
Ms Nishigandha! Ms Nishigandha!

27:38.160 --> 27:40.280
Well, sir, young Pawan has apologised.

27:40.360 --> 27:42.880
Are you willing to testify
in his favour now? Yeah?

27:43.480 --> 27:44.920
- [chuckles] Good job.
- Great. Thank you, sir.

27:45.000 --> 27:46.040
- Good.
- Thanks.

27:46.120 --> 27:48.800
You know, I read somewhere once,

27:49.760 --> 27:52.960
"Show me the heroes
the youth of your country look up to

27:53.040 --> 27:55.320
and I'll tell you
the future of your country."

27:57.480 --> 27:59.200
I hope he finds better heroes.

27:59.920 --> 28:01.240
India has plenty of them.

28:02.800 --> 28:03.760
[Vishwas] So Mr, Kumar,

28:04.440 --> 28:06.560
your son's turned over a new leaf.

28:06.640 --> 28:08.080
- Shall I tell you something?
- Yeah.

28:08.160 --> 28:10.080
This thing about taking him
to an adult jail

28:10.160 --> 28:11.560
was Advocate Ananya Shroff's idea.

28:11.640 --> 28:13.560
So you have to testify
in her favour, right?

28:13.640 --> 28:16.040
- Yes, Uncle.
- Sir, but I convinced him to study.

28:16.120 --> 28:17.240
Yeah, but that didn't work, right?

28:17.320 --> 28:18.560
Madam, madam.

28:19.120 --> 28:21.360
Both of you have
saved Pawan's life together.

28:22.080 --> 28:24.160
That's why I'll testify for both of you.

28:24.240 --> 28:25.520
- What?
- Yes.

28:25.600 --> 28:26.960
- He bought the deal.
- Thank you, sir.

28:27.040 --> 28:28.920
- And he didn't.
- That's useless, sir.

28:29.000 --> 28:30.640
- Correct.
- Only one of us can win this.

28:30.720 --> 28:32.120
Her side.

28:32.200 --> 28:33.720
But today I have won, madam.

28:36.080 --> 28:39.520
My son will be back home after six months.

28:43.160 --> 28:45.040
I suggest you both get together

28:45.120 --> 28:47.200
and sort out this Banaspati matter
once and for all.

28:47.280 --> 28:48.440
Come on.

28:48.520 --> 28:49.760
- Get together?
- Sir…

28:49.840 --> 28:51.000
- Sir…
- How will this work?

28:51.080 --> 28:52.200
Well, it didn't work.

28:53.120 --> 28:55.480
But you were tolerable for the first time.

28:55.560 --> 28:56.480
Mr Banaspati.

28:57.080 --> 28:58.440
And you weren't a total bitch today.

28:58.520 --> 29:00.720
- Mr Banaspati.
- Don't think I'll go easy on you,

29:00.800 --> 29:02.320
- Mr Banaspati.
- Of course not.

29:02.400 --> 29:03.320
Snakes don't have a heart.

29:03.400 --> 29:04.720
Mr Banaspati.

29:06.880 --> 29:08.960
- Hey!
- What are you doing?

29:09.040 --> 29:11.440
Now you can both get together
and pounce on me.

29:11.520 --> 29:13.520
- Mr Banaspati…
- You both are a match, by the way.

29:13.600 --> 29:15.080
- We both are a match?
- Yes, a perfect match.

29:15.160 --> 29:16.400
Because of you, I couldn't…

29:16.480 --> 29:18.920
Hey, don't do that here.
The kids will call you a wimp.

29:19.440 --> 29:20.440
It's burning!

29:20.520 --> 29:22.360
Didn't I say you can't meet him?
No, the judge is not available.

29:22.440 --> 29:24.280
I just need
to see him for a minute, please.

29:24.360 --> 29:25.600
[guard] Didn't you hear what I just said?

29:25.680 --> 29:27.920
- Hey, hey. It's okay. Let him in.
- Sir.

29:28.840 --> 29:30.760
- Okay, go.
- What is it?

29:30.840 --> 29:32.000
- Sir.
- Yes?

29:32.080 --> 29:36.440
We haven't had enough food to eat
for the last five months.

29:36.520 --> 29:39.000
You helped set up my food cart again.

29:39.080 --> 29:40.400
Food cart?

29:41.280 --> 29:43.080
Your Honour,
gate number 7 used to be open.

29:43.160 --> 29:45.080
- Yeah.
- So the carts couldn't be set up there.

29:45.160 --> 29:45.960
Oh.

29:46.040 --> 29:49.200
Today you signed an order that
a 60-mm lock should be put on the gate.

29:49.280 --> 29:50.960
So, that's why…

29:51.040 --> 29:54.440
Sir, I make very good
deep-fried savouries.

29:55.240 --> 29:56.800
So when I started today,

29:57.360 --> 29:59.920
I made the very first batch just for you.

30:01.240 --> 30:02.880
Would you like to try it?

30:08.000 --> 30:18.000
ভুয়া লিংক এড়িয়ে চলুন — অফিসিয়াল: -=[ MyFlixBD.com ]=-

30:09.400 --> 30:11.280
- Why not?
- [chuckling]

30:13.280 --> 30:14.400
Thank you, sir.

30:15.080 --> 30:16.640
- Take care of yourself.
- Yes, sir.

30:33.360 --> 30:35.000
- [Tyagi] Mr Shubhkela.
- Hmm?

30:35.640 --> 30:37.280
You know the line in that film,

30:37.360 --> 30:40.360
"A judge's pen can change destinies."

30:40.440 --> 30:42.160
Hmm, hmm.

30:42.240 --> 30:44.000
- Such a beautiful line.
- Excellent.

30:45.160 --> 30:47.360
You must select that one
for best film, please.

30:47.440 --> 30:48.840
[chuckles] Okay.

30:48.920 --> 30:52.040
And Topo,
all the paperwork that's pending,

30:52.120 --> 30:55.480
bring it to me, I want to sign everything
before I leave. Hmm?

30:57.120 --> 30:58.120
[Law] Come on, ma'am.

30:58.800 --> 31:00.120
You deleted your account?

31:00.200 --> 31:03.240
[clicks tongue] Couldn't you have waited
till the annual sale? Here.

31:03.320 --> 31:05.640
Law, I was thinking
we need to win on our own steam.

31:06.600 --> 31:09.160
I don't want to play cheap tricks
to get my name on the board.

31:09.240 --> 31:11.000
Enough now. How many more?

31:11.760 --> 31:13.040
Go get the scooter out.

31:17.920 --> 31:18.920
[phone buzzes]

31:21.160 --> 31:24.600
MINTU:
I WAS THINKING ABOUT YOU.
